review_blob: Was meant to buy the bottle only, but this one is actually far better than I supposed. Nice hints of malt and honey, rather than grainy like bud. The taste was fresh and flavorful, too. As the smells suggested.

The taste is a bit like winter melon punch. (!?)
Light boided and flat carbonation.
Overall I think the hoppy character is too low.

Aroma: Citrus and mango.
Appearance: Clear pale ale like.
Taste: This is the most disappoint part for this beer. It had weeds and earth flavor!? I suppose the hoppness wasnt well balanced.
